  • Class
    Description
    Extension<T extends Extension.Data>

    Extensions

    Implementations of this interface, that are registered by Javas service provider interface, will be called in JDACBuilder to configure the framework.

    Extension.Data
    Implementations of this interface are providing additional configuration to implementations of Extension.
    ExtensionException
    A sub exception of ConfigurationException that can be implemented by users of the library for throwing own exceptions during the initialization of Extensions or in PropertyProvider.supplier().
    ExtensionException.Information
    The information object holding information like the Bundle name to use.
    ExtensionFilter
    A Predicate to test whether an Extension should be loaded or not.
    ExtensionFilter.FilterStrategy
    The two available filter strategies
    Property<T>

    Properties

    An Property represent either...

    Property.Category
    The category of a property defines how values for it can be provided.
    Property.Enumeration<E>
    A Property.Enumeration property basically represents a Collection of multiple values.
    Property.FallbackBehaviour
    The fallback behaviour defines whether the fallback value provided by JDA-Commands should be accumulated together with the user defined ones or overwritten.
    Property.Map<K,V>
    A Property.Map property basically represents a Map, where each value belongs target a specific key.
    Property.Singleton<T>
    A Property.Singleton property just hols one value.
    PropertyProvider<T>

    PropertyProviders

    An PropertyProvider provides values for the Property associated with it.

    PropertyProvider.Context
    This context provides useful functionality to a PropertyProvider during value creation.
